  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SAFETY OFFICER",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Main Duties of a Construction Safety Officer</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>1. Site Safety Management</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure all construction activities comply with the <strong>Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) Act</strong>, <strong>MOM regulations</strong>, and company safety policies.</li>\n  <li>Conduct <strong>daily site safety inspections</strong> and identify unsafe practices or conditions.</li>\n  <li>Stop work immediately if serious safety violations or life-threatening conditions are observed.</li>\n  <li>Monitor high-risk activities such as lifting operations, confined space entry, hot works, and work-at-height.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>2. Safety Documentation &amp; Reporting</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and maintain <strong>Safety Reports</strong>, <strong>Risk Assessments (RA)</strong>, <strong>Safe Work Procedures (SWP)</strong>, and <strong>Permit-to-Work (PTW)</strong> records.</li>\n  <li>Keep updated records of <strong>accident reports</strong>, <strong>near-miss incidents</strong>, and <strong>safety statistics</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Assist in preparation for <strong>audits</strong> and <strong>inspections</strong> by authorities or clients.</li>\n  <li>Maintain safety-related documentation such as MSDS (Material Safety Data Sheets) for hazardous materials.</li>\n</ul>",
